{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":59983,"duration_api_ms":59945,"num_turns":9,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"78a1e813-cb3d-4501-aa5a-d01fcc86ac69","total_cost_usd":0.3316757,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28008,"cache_read_input_tokens":185107,"output_tokens":2220,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":28008,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":2220,"cacheReadInputTokens":185107,"cacheCreationInputTokens":28008,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.3231385,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":10,"outputTokens":348,"cacheReadInputTokens":25672,"cacheCreationInputTokens":3376,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.008537200000000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All four amendments identify real defects verified against the source code. The timestamp regression (fr-4-54b5dd71), code duplication (fr-4-65a16a24), legacy backward-compatibility breakage (fr-4-0195eaea), and start idempotency gap (fr-4-013c9cb2) are all confirmed by tracing the actual control flow in service.rs and fs.rs.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-4-54b5dd71","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed at service.rs:590-591. `snapshot.updated_at` is unconditionally set to `finalized_run.finished_at.unwrap_or(finished_at)`, which on a replay reuses the original completion timestamp. If any intervening operation advanced `updated_at`, this assignment regresses it. A monotonic guard like `snapshot.updated_at = snapshot.updated_at.max(finished_at)` is the correct fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-4-65a16a24","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified that `same_attempt` (fs.rs:2301) is identical to `task_runs_same_attempt` (service.rs:134), `merge_attempt_rows` (fs.rs:2317) is identical to `merge_task_run_attempt` (service.rs:140), and `collapse_runs_for_bead` (fs.rs:2373) shares the same merge algorithm as `normalize_task_runs` (service.rs:157) differing only by a bead_id pre-filter. The merge logic is subtle (field backfilling, consumed-start tracking) and having two copies risks silent divergence when either is updated independently. Extracting a shared helper is a sound improvement."},{"amendment_id":"fr-4-0195eaea","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by tracing the no-run_id selector path (fs.rs:2557-2581). For a legacy two-row attempt (running + terminal, no run_id), the running row is classified as a superseded legacy start by `is_superseded_legacy_start` and filtered out, while the terminal row is excluded by the `!is_terminal()` filter. This yields zero open_matches, producing an ambiguous-update error instead of allowing the replay to repair snapshot/journal state. This directly contradicts the service contract documented at service.rs:545-548."},{"amendment_id":"fr-4-013c9cb2","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed at service.rs:456-466. `append_task_run` executes before `write_snapshot`, so a crash between these two calls leaves a running row in the NDJSON file. A retry of `record_bead_start` with the same `run_id` appends a second running row. Later, `update_task_run` at fs.rs:2510-2555 finds multiple exact run_id matches and falls into the ambiguous-error branch (line 2548-2554), permanently stranding the bead. The start path needs deduplication (upsert or check-before-append) to be safe under retries."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"49358122-3432-4f65-9d81-bb0acb246b16"}
